# NIRD Design System

Inspired by Juliette Taka's "Emerald" theme for Debian 12.

## Color Palette

### Primary Colors (Village/NIRD - The Heroes)

| Color | Hex | CSS Variable | Usage |
|-------|-----|--------------|-------|
| Emerald Green | `#00997d` | `--color-emerald` | Primary buttons, success states |
| Forest Green | `#2E7D32` | `--color-forest` | Secondary actions |
| Gold | `#F9A825` | `--color-gold` | Magic Potion accents, highlights |
| Parchment | `#FFF8E1` | `--color-parchment` | Light backgrounds |
| Soft White | `#f4f4f9` | `--color-soft-white` | Text backgrounds |

### Empire Colors (Big Tech - The Villains)

| Color | Hex | CSS Variable | Usage |
|-------|-----|--------------|-------|
| Roman Red | `#C62828` | `--color-roman-red` | Danger, enemy elements |
| Resistance Orange | `#ff8c00` | `--color-orange` | CTAs, alerts |
| Dark Blue | `#1A237E` | `--color-empire-blue` | Corporate, serious |
| Steel Gray | `#455A64` | `--color-steel` | Industrial elements |

### Technology Colors

| Color | Hex | CSS Variable | Usage |
|-------|-----|--------------|-------|
| Slate Blue | `#4a697d` | `--color-slate` | Backgrounds, footer |
| Deep Mineral | `#1a1a1d` | `--color-mineral` | Dark mode |

## Visual Metaphor Rules

### Village Elements (Use NIRD Colors)
- Buttons for positive actions → Emerald Green
- Success messages → Forest Green
- Special features/highlights → Gold
- Backgrounds → Parchment/Soft White

### Empire Elements (Use Empire Colors)
- Warning about Big Tech → Roman Red
- Statistics about problems → Steel Gray
- Corporate imagery → Dark Blue

